      "text": " We next prove that  $\\lim_{t\\to 0^+} \\frac{(h_{W_t}-h_K)(u)}{t} = f(u)$ , for  $S_K$ -almost every  $u$  (the proof on the left of 0 is similar). Let  $l_d(u) = \\lim_{t \\to 0^+} \\frac{(h_{W_t} - h_K)(u)}{t}$ , which is well-defined for all  $u \\in \\mathbb{S}^{n-1}$ , by concavity. Note that (by definition of  $W_t$ ),  $l_d(u) \\leq f(u)$ , for all  $u$ . Let  $U_{\\epsilon} = {u \\in \\mathbb{S}^{n-1} : l_d(u) < f(u) - \\epsilon}$ . It is enough to show that  $S_K(U_{\\epsilon}) = 0$  (for arbitrary  $\\epsilon > 0$ ).",
